header.gameNote: SAN JUAN SHOOTOUT AT SAN JUAN PR

article.headline: Akron 83, Mississippi St. 72
article.story: GUAYNABO, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Dru Joyce made five 3-pointers and had 16 points to lead Akron to an 83-72 victory over Mississippi State at the San Juan Shootout on Tuesday night. Akron (5-2) jumped out to an early lead and led 40-28 at halftime. Mississippi State (8-3) trailed by as many as 18 with less than 15 minutes left. The Bulldogs closed to 69-62 after Walter Sharpe hit two free throws with 3:52 remaining. Joyce countered with a 3-pointer that stretched Akron's lead to 72-62. Nick Dials led Akron with 16 points and three steals, and Bubba Walther added 15 points. Jamall Edmondson scored 17 points for Mississippi State. Akron plays undefeated Clemson (10-0) in the tournament title game on Wednesday. Mississippi State will face Holy Cross (5-5) in the third-place game.
